  "text": "The implementation of a minimal GCC GIMPLE optimization pass that counts basic blocks per function was created following established GCC patterns found in the codebase. The key architectural components are defined in gcc/tree-pass.h, which provides the pass_data struct (containing metadata like type GIMPLE_PASS, name, optinfo_flags, tv_id, and properties) and the gimple_opt_pass class (inheriting from opt_pass). The pass class defines virtual methods gate() and execute() following the pattern established in gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc (the Dead Code Elimination pass) and gcc/tree-call-cdce.cc (the Conditional Dead Call Elimination pass). The execute() method iterates through basic blocks using the FOR_EACH_BB_FN macro defined in gcc/tree-cfg.h, counts them, and outputs debug information via dump_file (declared in gcc/dumpfile.h) when available. The timevar ID TV_TREE_SSA_OTHER (defined in gcc/timevar.def) is used as a generic tree SSA pass timer. The pass is registered via a make_pass_count_bb() factory function following GCC's established pattern of pass registration in gcc/tree-pass.h. The implementation includes proper header guards, GCC licensing headers, and C++ namespace encapsulation matching GCC conventions. Both a source file (count_basic_blocks_pass.cc) and header file (count_basic_blocks_pass.h) were created to define and declare the pass components."
}

